nodes.text: I have consistently had the problem where I selected a flight, and clicked the "Select" button, only to be told that the price had suddenly risen by hundreds of dollars.
dwilson99(1055): I have consistently had the problem where I selected a flight, and clicked the "Select" button, only to be told that the price had suddenly risen by hundreds of dollars.
Annot: I have consistently had the problem where I selected a flight, and clicked the "Select" button, only to be told that the price had suddenly risen by hundreds of dollars.
It's the old "bait and switch".
dwilson99(1055): It's the old "bait and switch".
Annot: It's the old "bait and switch".
When I cancel and start over again, I see the same thing: a lowball offer, with a much higher price when I try to buy the ticket.
dwilson99(1055): When I cancel and start over again, I see the same thing: a lowball offer, with a much higher price when I try to buy the ticket.
Annot: When I cancel and start over again, I see the same thing: a lowball offer, with a much higher price when I try to buy the ticket.
Airlines (or travel agencies such as Travelocity) should be required to honor the offered price for at least some number of minutes  at least 10 minutes.
dwilson99(1055): Airlines (or travel agencies such as Travelocity) should be required to honor the offered price for at least some number of minutes  at least 10 minutes.
Annot: Airlines (or travel agencies such as Travelocity) should be required to honor the offered price for at least some number of minutes  at least 10 minutes.
If the flight sells out while I'm deciding then fine, but the price I get should be the price I'm offered  if there is a seat still available.
dwilson99(1055): If the flight sells out while I'm deciding then fine, but the price I get should be the price I'm offered  if there is a seat still available.
Annot: If the flight sells out while I'm deciding then fine, but the price I get should be the price I'm offered  if there is a seat still available.
No bait and switch while you're online.
dwilson99(1055): No bait and switch while you're online.
Annot: No bait and switch while you're online.
The price of fuel doesn't change while I am trying to book a flight.
darawayne(1071): The price of fuel doesn't change while I am trying to book a flight.
Annot: The price of fuel doesn't change while I am trying to book a flight.
Maybe airlines should only be allowed to change prices once a week, or once a day, always at midnight, or something like that.
darawayne(1071): Maybe airlines should only be allowed to change prices once a week, or once a day, always at midnight, or something like that.
Annot: Maybe airlines should only be allowed to change prices once a week, or once a day, always at midnight, or something like that.
It is extremely frustrating to try to buy a ticket and have availability and/or price change while you are pushing the "Buy" button.
